included.description:
Worked on designing a mobile application for the context-based intuitive information for effective presentation of alerts can assist humans to interact more effectively with the system. Applied all the intuitive principles related to the mobile design while prototyping the application. Design patterns used in developing the application can provide context driven alerts for understanding that certain situation is important.
Worked on gathering the requirements from the students to develop the application. Worked on the methodology and the framework of evaluation for intuitive design. Created wireframes for the application using Wireframe Sketcher Wire frame tool. Created the usage scenarios, task flows, site map to explain the flow of the application. Human factor principles and cognitive principles are followed while designed the application. Developed prototype using MIT APP Inventor to show the different alerts based on the context. Analyze the prototype by doing heuristic evaluation and reported the results.
included.title: Design Patterns for Intuitive Interaction of Context-Based Alerts on Mobile Devices.

included.description: I have worked on creating a prototype for mobile app called BuddyScheduler. As part of the course work, i were asked to come up with an idea and prototype for a mobile app. I want to develop an app which could take care of scheduling events among a group of friends when scheduling events like going to movies, restaurants etc. I started with the basic requirements like user being able to register, login and initiate a request for an event. As part of the requirements gathering I prepared a questionnaire and distributed among my classmates to better understand the others point of view. This exercise helped me a lot and was able to refine my requirements. I prepared the use case diagrams which helped me in defining the scope of the project. I also worked on the design part to identify the major components and cameup with 3 tier architectural pattern identifying the componenets in each of front end, middle and back end partitions. I used the Axure prototyping tool to create the interactive wireframes. I was able to create different screens to accomodate for the various features of the app. All the screens were created with interactive controls like buttons, textboxes and data validation was carried wherever necessary. More emphasis was given on the usability guidelines and created screens with high fidelity. I was able to publish the prototype using the inbuilt publish feature 'AxShare' of Axure to view it online
